The mound is believed to be a round tumulus with a diameter of 14 meters (possibly a square tumulus with sides of 14 meters). It features a {{ill|yokoana-shiki sekkaku|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber}} with double-sleeve construction. {{Sfn|Survey of Large Late Kofun in Nankoku|2006|pp=5-11, 23-29}}
The dimensions of the stone chamber are as follows: {{Sfn|Survey of Large Late Kofun in Nankoku|2006|pp=1-4, 5-11, 23-29}}{{Sfn|Maibun Kōchi No. 25|2012|p=7}} * Total chamber length: 8.96 meters * Burial chamber: Length 5.64 meters, width 2.16 meters (rear wall), width 2.14 meters (entrance), height 2.8 meters * Entrance passage: Length 3.32 meters, width 1.20 meters
The chamber has been plundered, but remains of {{ill|Sue pottery|ja|須恵器|1=Sue pottery}} and jewelry have been discovered. {{Sfn|Maibun Kōchi No. 25|2012|p=7}} The tumulus is estimated to date back to the late 6th to early 7th century. {{Sfn|Maibun Kōchi No. 25|2012|p=7}}
