=== Kofun No. 3 === [[File:Myokenhikoyama-kofun 3-1.JPG|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Entrance to the stone chamber of Kofun No. 3}}]] [[File:Myoken Hikoyama Kofun Group-3, 3D-B.jpg|thumb|250px|right|{{center|Overview of the stone chamber in Kofun No. 3}}]] '''Myōkenhikoyama Kofun No. 3''' ({{Coord|33|34|17.81|N|133|37|1.18|E|region:JP-39_type:landmark|name=Myōkenhikoyama Kofun No. 3}}) is located approximately 200 meters northeast of No. 1 kofun. It is a round tumulus with a diameter of 5 meters and a height of 2.3 meters, featuring a double-sleeve {{ill|yokoana-shiki sekkaku|ja|横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|2=ja|3=横穴式石室|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|4=zh|5=橫穴式石室|6=ko|7=굴식 돌방무덤|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|1=Corridor-Style Stone Chamber|qq=draft}}. <ref name="Explanation Board">Historical site explanation board.</ref>
The dimensions of the stone chamber are: {{Sfn|Myōkenhikoyama Kofun Group (Heibonsha)|1983}} * Total chamber length: 5.8 meters * Entrance passage length: 1.8 meters
Artifacts such as human bones, Sue pottery, straight swords, daggers, horse fittings, iron sickles, iron plow blades, magatama, and tubular beads were unearthed from within the chamber. <ref name="Explanation Board"/> The tumulus is estimated to have been constructed in the late 6th century. <ref name="Explanation Board"/>
<gallery> Myoken Hikoyama Kofun Group-3, 3D-N.jpg|Stone chamber layout Myoken Hikoyama Kofun Group-3, sekishitsu-1.jpg|Main chamber (towards the rear wall) Myoken Hikoyama Kofun Group-3, sekishitsu-2.jpg|Main chamber (towards the entrance) </gallery>
